verses.roman:
rāmānanda āilā pāche dolāya caḍiyā
vāṇīnātha bahu prasāda dila pāṭhāñā

synonyms: rāmānanda—Rāmānanda Rāya; āilā—came; pāche—behind; dolāya caḍiyā—riding on a palanquin; vāṇīnātha—Vāṇīnātha Rāya; bahu—a large quantity of; prasāda—remnants of the food of Jagannātha; dila—gave; pāṭhāñā—sending.
translation: After Lord Caitanya reached Bhavānīpura, Rāmānanda Rāya arrived on his palanquin, and Vāṇīnātha Rāya had a large quantity of prasāda sent to the Lord.
